We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.

.
View all three films via link in profile.
.

HOME TOUR | Les Voisine
​.
​Made up of three distinct yet interconnected houses, Les Voisines by  @appareilarchitecture blurs the line between shared and private spaces.
​.
​Meaning ‘The Neighbours’ in French, Les Voisines adopts an unconventional co-living layout. Secluded in the unfrequented forests of Quebec, the home offers a retreat for both inhabiting parties – a space where they can come together while remaining sufficiently apart.
​.
​Read more about Les Voisine on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Architecture @appareilarchitecture 
​Interior Design @lysannepepin
​Photography @michaudfelix_photo
​Words @hollybeadle 
​.

​.
Sydney design duo Shannon Shlom and Dominique Brammah, the names behind recently established studio @we_are_duet, introduce a balance of honest materials, warm tones and bold details to their Watson House redesign.

​.

node.text:
THE ICON | Up Series
​.
The late 1960s was a time when designers often threw caution to the wind, pushing boundaries and going where others haven’t. This is certainly the case with Gaetano Pesce’s Up Series, Numbers Up 5 and Up 6, launched at the Milan Furniture Fair in 1969.
​.
The bulbous-shaped chair, with its connected ottoman, is a​lso referred to as ‘La Mamma’, ‘Big Mama’ and ‘Dona’.
.
​Initially produced in five colours and two bold striped patterns, the latter accentuating its form, it’s now available in more bold and punchy primary colours, including red, and is a dramatic highlight and sculptural piece in any room.
​.
​Read more about the Up Series Chair on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
The Up Series Chair, as featured in Emerald Terrace by @chelsea_hing.
​Photography @inbedwith.me
Styling @arielcoop 
​Words #stephencrafti 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/the-icon-up-series-chair/

​.
​@vipp has recently unveiled their latest venture, converting a 100-year-old pencil factory into a dining experience for chefs to share their talent through pop up 'supper clubs'.
​.
​On designing the space, interior designer Julie Cloos Moelsgaard says she experimented with a mix of @vipp classics and new designs. "Vipp Pencil Factory acts as sort of a testing lab where we can try out new ideas, forms and materials in unconventional ways," Julie says.
​.
